title: open
definition: Make a resource visible or active for interaction.

title: close
definition: Hide or deactivate a resource, ending interaction.

title: create
definition: Instantiate a new object or record.
examples: create a folder; create new note

title: delete
definition: Remove an object or record so it no longer exists.

title: save
definition: Persist current state to storage.

title: edit
definition: Modify the properties or content of an object.

title: rename
definition: Change an object's identifier or label.

title: move
definition: Change an object's location or ordering.
examples: move to folder A; move row up

title: copy
definition: Duplicate an object to a new location.

title: paste
definition: Insert clipboard contents at the target location.

title: now
definition: Constrain to the present moment or immediate execution.

title: today
definition: Constrain to the current calendar day.

title: tomorrow
definition: Constrain to the next calendar day.

title: before
definition: Times strictly earlier than a reference point.

title: after
definition: Times strictly later than a reference point.

title: between
definition: Closed interval between two times.

title: until
definition: Times up to and including a limit.

title: during
definition: Within a named span or event window.

title: recurring
definition: Indicates the time repeats on a schedule.

title: deadline
definition: Specifies a completion time limit.

title: exactly
definition: Specify an exact numeric or categorical match.

title: approximately
definition: Specify an inexact or close value.

title: at_least
definition: Lower bound inclusive.

title: at_most
definition: Upper bound inclusive.

title: greater_than
definition: Strictly larger than a reference value.

title: less_than
definition: Strictly smaller than a reference value.

title: equal
definition: Equality comparison to a reference value.

title: between_values
definition: Closed interval with two numeric bounds.

title: top_n
definition: Select the highest-ranked N items.

title: percent
definition: Express a proportion out of 100.

title: Conditional 'if'
definition: Introduces a condition that must be met for the subsequent action to be executed.

title: Negative 'unless'
definition: Introduces a negative condition; the action occurs only if the condition is not met.

title: Alternative 'otherwise'
definition: Specifies an alternative action to be taken if the primary condition is not met.

title: Prerequisite 'as long as'
definition: Specifies a continuous condition that must remain true for the action to be valid.

title: Proactive 'in case'
definition: Introduces a potential future condition for which a preparatory action is taken.
examples: in case|just in case|on the off chance

title: Exclusive 'only if'
definition: Specifies that the condition is the only one under which the action will occur.

title: Premise 'given that'
definition: Introduces a known fact or premise from which the subsequent action logically follows.

title: Assumed 'assuming'
definition: Introduces a condition that is assumed to be true for the purpose of the action.

title: Requirement 'requires'
definition: States a mandatory prerequisite or input for an action or process.

title: Absence 'without'
definition: Specifies a condition of absence; the action proceeds if something is not present.

title: Contingency
definition: Specifies that an action is dependent on the outcome of another event.
examples: contingent on|dependent on|pending the outcome of

title: Exception
definition: Introduces an exception to a general rule or statement.

title: Unconditional
definition: Specifies that an action should proceed irrespective of other conditions.

title: Immediate Trigger
definition: Specifies an action that should occur immediately upon the fulfillment of a condition.

title: Sufficiency
definition: Specifies a condition that, if met, is sufficient to cause a certain outcome.
examples: is sufficient to|is enough to|suffices for

title: Necessity
definition: Specifies a condition that is a necessary prerequisite for an outcome.
examples: is necessary for|is required for|can't happen without

title: Retrospective
definition: Frames a condition in the past that, had it been different, would have changed an outcome.
examples: if it weren't for|had it not been for

title: Default Action
definition: Specifies a default action to be taken if no other conditions apply.
examples: by default|as a fallback|if nothing else

title: Possibility
definition: Indicates a proposition is possible but not certain.

title: Probability
definition: Indicates a proposition is likely to be true but not guaranteed.

title: Certainty
definition: Indicates a proposition is known or asserted to be definitely true.

title: Verified Claim
definition: Indicates a proposition has been verified or is confirmed by evidence.

title: Disputed Claim
definition: Indicates a proposition is contested, debated, or unproven.

title: Assumption
definition: Frames a proposition as an assumption taken for granted without proof.

title: Hearsay / Reported
definition: Indicates information is from an external source and not directly known.

title: Impossibility
definition: Indicates a proposition is asserted to be impossible or certainly false.

title: Self-Evident
definition: Indicates a proposition is obvious or requires no proof.

title: Theoretical
definition: Frames a proposition as existing in theory but not necessarily in practice.

title: Plausibility
definition: Indicates that a proposition is reasonable and could well be true.

title: Conclusive
definition: Indicates that the evidence is decisive and settles a question beyond doubt.

title: Intuitive Belief
definition: Frames a proposition as based on intuition or a gut feeling rather than explicit evidence.

title: Unconfirmed
definition: Indicates that a proposition is currently lacking verification.

title: Empirical Evidence
definition: Indicates that a claim is based on observation or direct experience.

title: Subjective Belief
definition: Explicitly frames a statement as a personal opinion or belief.

title: Common Knowledge
definition: Frames a proposition as being widely known and accepted.
examples: it is known that|as everyone knows|traditionally

title: Counterintuitive
definition: Indicates that a proposition is true despite appearing to be contrary to what one would expect.

title: Inference
definition: To reach a conclusion on the basis of evidence and reasoning.

title: Speculation
definition: To form a theory or hypothesis without firm evidence.

title: Realization
definition: The act of suddenly understanding or becoming aware of something.
examples: realize|it dawned on me|I see now

title: Reconsideration
definition: To think about something again, often to change one's mind.

title: Doubt
definition: To feel uncertain about something or question its truth.

title: Judgment
definition: To form an opinion or conclusion about something.

title: Reflection
definition: To think deeply or carefully about something.

title: Recall / Remember
definition: To bring a fact, event, or situation back into one's mind.

title: Forget
definition: To be unable to remember a fact, event, or piece of information.

title: Understanding
definition: To perceive the intended meaning of words, a language, or a speaker.

title: Misunderstanding
definition: To fail to understand something correctly.

title: Prioritization
definition: To determine the order for dealing with tasks according to their importance.

title: Anticipation
definition: The act of expecting or predicting a future event or outcome.

title: Analysis
definition: The process of breaking down a complex topic into smaller parts for better understanding.

title: Synthesis
definition: The act of combining separate elements to form a coherent whole.

title: Association
definition: The mental act of connecting or linking one idea or memory with another.

title: Differentiation
definition: The act of distinguishing or perceiving the difference between things.

title: Visualization
definition: The act of forming a mental image of something.

title: Abstraction
definition: The process of considering something as a general quality or idea apart from specific instances.

title: Classification
definition: The act of arranging a group of items into classes or categories.

title: Clarification
definition: Signals that the following statement is intended to clarify a previous one.
examples: to clarify|in other words|let me rephrase

title: Correction
definition: Signals that the following statement corrects a previous error.

title: Aside
definition: Frames a statement as a digression or parenthetical comment.

title: Exemplification
definition: Introduces an example to illustrate a point.

title: Summarization
definition: Signals that the following statement is a summary of previous points.

title: Topic Shift
definition: Explicitly signals a change in the topic of conversation.
examples: changing the subject|moving on|on another note

title: Topic Return
definition: Signals a return to a previous topic after a digression.
examples: to get back on topic|as I was saying|returning to

title: Elaboration
definition: Indicates that more detail or information will be provided on a point.
examples: to elaborate|in more detail|to expand on that

title: Emphasis
definition: Used to stress the importance or significance of the following point.

title: Conclusion
definition: Signals the final point or closing of a discussion.

title: Preamble
definition: Introduces a topic or frames the context before the main statement.
examples: first of all|to begin|as a preface

title: Context Setting
definition: Provides background or context for the main statement that follows.
examples: for context|to set the scene|as background

title: Follow-up
definition: Signals that the statement builds upon a previous point or interaction.
examples: as a follow-up|building on that|to add to that

title: Reiteration
definition: Signals an intentional repetition of a point for emphasis or clarity.
examples: to reiterate|let me repeat|as I said before

title: Simplification
definition: Indicates that a complex idea is being expressed in simpler terms.
examples: in simple terms|to put it simply|in a nutshell

title: Acknowledgement
definition: Acknowledges the validity or existence of another's point before proceeding.
examples: that's a valid point|I see what you mean|point taken

title: Concession
definition: Acknowledges a point from an opposing argument, often before a rebuttal.
examples: I concede|while it's true that|I'll grant you

title: Disclaiming
definition: A statement used to distance the speaker from a potential misinterpretation.
examples: not to oversimplify|this may be obvious, but

title: Framing
definition: Sets the perspective or frame through which a statement should be interpreted.
examples: from a technical perspective|speaking as a user

title: Joy / Happiness
definition: A positive emotional state characterized by feelings of pleasure, contentment, and elation.

title: Sadness / Sorrow
definition: An emotional state of unhappiness, typically resulting from loss, disappointment, or grief.

title: Anger / Frustration
definition: A strong feeling of annoyance, displeasure, or hostility.

title: Fear / Anxiety
definition: An unpleasant emotion caused by the belief that someone or something is dangerous or threatening.

title: Surprise / Astonishment
definition: A brief state of emotion experienced as the result of an unexpected event.

title: Trust / Confidence
definition: A feeling of confidence and security in the reliability, truth, or ability of someone or something.

title: Anticipation / Eagerness
definition: A state of looking forward with excitement or expectation to a future event.

title: Serenity / Calm
definition: A state of being calm, peaceful, and untroubled.

title: Intrigue / Curiosity
definition: A state of interest or fascination that prompts a desire to know or learn more.

title: Ambivalence / Conflict
definition: The state of having mixed, contradictory, or conflicting emotional responses toward something.

title: Relief
definition: A feeling of reassurance and relaxation following release from anxiety or distress.

title: Disappointment
definition: A feeling of sadness or displeasure caused by the nonfulfillment of one's hopes or expectations.

title: Empathy / Resonance
definition: The capacity to understand or feel what another person is experiencing from within their frame of reference.

title: Contentment / Satisfaction
definition: A state of peaceful happiness and satisfaction with one's situation.

title: Enthusiasm / Excitement
definition: A state of intense and eager enjoyment, interest, or approval.

title: Rage / Fury
definition: An intense, explosive, and often uncontrolled state of anger. (High-intensity emo003)

title: Ecstasy / Elation
definition: An overwhelming feeling of great happiness or joyful excitement. (High-intensity emo001)

title: Grief / Despair
definition: Intense sorrow, especially in response to a profound loss, often coupled with a sense of hopelessness. (High-intensity emo002)

title: Terror / Panic
definition: An overwhelming, sudden, and disabling feeling of fear. (High-intensity emo004)

title: Loathing / Disgust
definition: A feeling of intense dislike or revulsion.

title: Admiration / Veneration
definition: A feeling of deep respect, approval, or reverence for someone or something. (High-intensity emo006)

title: Pride / Triumph
definition: A feeling of deep pleasure or satisfaction derived from one's own achievements or qualities.

title: Shame / Humiliation
definition: A painful feeling of humiliation or distress caused by the consciousness of wrong or foolish behavior.

title: Guilt / Remorse
definition: A feeling of having done wrong or failed in an obligation, accompanied by a sense of responsibility.

title: Jealousy / Envy
definition: The state of feeling or showing envy of someone or their achievements and advantages, or resentment against a rival.

title: Gratitude / Thankfulness
definition: The quality of being thankful; a readiness to show appreciation for and to return kindness.

title: Vulnerability
definition: The state of being exposed to the possibility of being attacked or harmed, either physically or emotionally.

title: Boredom / Apathy
definition: The state of feeling weary and restless through lack of interest.

title: Confusion / Bewilderment
definition: The state of being unable to think clearly or to understand something.

title: Hope / Optimism
definition: A feeling of expectation and desire for a certain thing to happen; confidence in future success.

title: Pessimism / Doubt
definition: A tendency to see the worst aspect of things or believe that the worst will happen; a lack of hope.

title: Nostalgia
definition: A sentimental longing or wistful affection for a period in the past.

title: Awe / Wonder
definition: A feeling of reverential respect mixed with fear or wonder, often in response to something vast or beautiful.

title: Support / Allyship
definition: To provide assistance, encouragement, or solidarity to another entity.

title: Opposition / Challenge
definition: To actively resist, question, or express disapproval of another entity or their position.

title: Deference / Following
definition: To yield to another's judgment, authority, or leadership.

title: Assertion / Leadership
definition: To take a position of guidance, authority, or control within a social dynamic.

title: Connection / Relating
definition: To establish a mutual bond or understanding with another entity.

title: Collaboration / Cooperation
definition: To work jointly with another entity toward a shared goal.

title: Exclusion / Ostracism
definition: To actively prevent an entity from being part of a group or activity.

title: Inclusion / Welcoming
definition: To actively bring an entity into a group or make them feel part of it.

title: Harmonization / Mediation
definition: To bring differing parties into agreement or resolve conflict between them.

title: Competition / Rivalry
definition: To strive against another entity to achieve a goal or superiority.

title: Affiliation / In-group
definition: To formally join or identify oneself with a group or cause.

title: Disaffiliation / Distancing
definition: To formally separate or distance oneself from a group or cause.

title: Delegation / Entrusting
definition: To assign a task or responsibility to another entity, typically one in a subordinate position.

title: Negotiation / Bargaining
definition: To hold a discussion with another entity in order to reach a formal agreement.

title: Reciprocation / Obligation
definition: To respond to a positive action with another positive action, often from a sense of social obligation.

title: Mentorship / Guidance
definition: To advise or train a less experienced person.

title: Protection / Guardianship
definition: To defend or keep another entity safe from harm.

title: Conformity
definition: To behave in accordance with socially accepted conventions or standards.

title: Dissent / Nonconformity
definition: To express opinions that are at variance with those commonly or officially held.

title: Gatekeeping
definition: To control access to a group, community, or area of knowledge.

title: Representation
definition: To act or speak officially for another person or group.
examples: represent|speak for|act on behalf of|advocate for

title: Emulation / Imitation
definition: To match or surpass a person or achievement, typically by imitation.
examples: emulate|imitate|model after|follow in the footsteps of

title: Disrespect / Undermining
definition: To act in a way that shows a lack of respect or courtesy; to weaken or subvert.

title: Reconciliation
definition: The restoration of friendly relations after a conflict.
examples: reconcile with|make amends|mend fences|bury the hatchet

title: Estrangement / Alienation
definition: The state of no longer being on friendly terms or part of a social group.

title: Accountability
definition: The act of taking or assigning responsibility for actions and outcomes.

title: Consent
definition: An explicit agreement or permission for something to happen or be done.

title: Objection / Principled Dissent
definition: To express disapproval or disagreement on ethical or moral grounds.

title: Boundary
definition: The act of defining a personal or social limit that should not be crossed.
examples: boundary|this is a limit|that's not acceptable

title: Respectful Framing
definition: A preface used to signal that a potentially challenging statement is intended to be respectful.
examples: with all due respect|respectfully|meaning no offense

title: Good Faith
definition: To act with sincere, honest, and fair intentions.

title: Responsibility
definition: The state of having a duty to deal with something or of having control over someone; moral accountability.

title: Inclusivity
definition: The practice of providing equal access and opportunity to people who might otherwise be excluded or marginalized.

title: Sustainability
definition: The act of operating in a way that avoids the long-term depletion of natural or social resources.
examples: sustainably|ethically sourced|with future impact in mind

title: Fairness / Justice
definition: Impartial and just treatment or behavior without favoritism or discrimination.

title: Harm Reduction
definition: A set of practical strategies and ideas aimed at reducing negative consequences.
examples: to reduce harm|do no harm|for safety|as a precaution

title: Integrity
definition: The quality of being honest and having strong moral principles.
examples: with integrity|on principle|as a matter of principle

title: Transparency
definition: The quality of being open, honest, and easy to understand in one's actions.

title: Due Diligence
definition: The reasonable steps a person should take before entering into an agreement or an action with another party.
examples: with due diligence|thoroughly vetted|after careful consideration

title: Conflict of Interest
definition: A situation in which the concerns or aims of two different parties are incompatible, raising ethical questions.

title: Confidentiality
definition: A set of rules or a promise that limits access or places restrictions on certain types of information.

title: Plausible Deniability
definition: The ability of people to deny knowledge of or responsibility for any damnable actions committed by others.

title: Unethical / Immoral
definition: An action or state that violates accepted principles of right and wrong.

title: Justified Action
definition: An action that is considered legitimate or acceptable because it is done for a good reason.

title: Proportionality
definition: The principle that an action's punishment or response should be commensurate with the severity of the offense.

title: Virtue / Moral Excellence
definition: Behavior showing high moral standards.

title: Apology / Acknowledgment
definition: A regretful acknowledgment of an offense or failure.
examples: I apologize|my apologies|I regret|acknowledging the harm

title: Restitution / Reparation
definition: The act of compensating for loss, damage, or injury; making amends.
examples: to make restitution|reparation|making it right|to compensate

title: Forgiveness
definition: A conscious, deliberate decision to release feelings of resentment or vengeance toward a person who has harmed you.

title: Whistleblowing
definition: The act of exposing any kind of information or activity that is deemed illegal, unethical, or not correct.

title: Intention
definition: Expresses a clear aim or plan to perform an action.
examples: intend to|my intention is|aim to|going to

title: Planning
definition: Indicates that an action is part of a considered plan or schedule.
examples: plan to|planning on|scheduled to|the plan is

title: Commitment / Vow
definition: Signals a firm promise or solemn pledge to perform an action.

title: Proposal
definition: To put forward an action or idea for consideration by others.

title: Goal / Objective
definition: Frames an action as the means to achieve a specific, desired outcome.
examples: the goal is|my objective is|in order to achieve

title: Willingness
definition: Expresses readiness or agreement to perform an action if needed or requested.

title: Desire / Wish
definition: Indicates a hope or want for an action to occur, without a firm plan or commitment.
examples: want to|wish to|would like to|hope to

title: Request
definition: The act of formally or politely asking for an action to be performed.

title: Offer
definition: To present an action for acceptance or rejection by another.

title: Prioritization
definition: The intent to treat a task or goal as more important than others.

title: Deprecation
definition: The intent to phase out or discourage the use of something, often while providing an alternative.

title: Escalation
definition: The intent to raise an issue or task to a higher level of authority or urgency for resolution.
examples: escalate|raise the issue|report up|flag for review

title: Veto / Rejection
definition: The intent to formally reject or forbid an action or proposal, often from a position of authority.

title: Refusal
definition: A stated intention to not perform a requested or expected action.

title: Hesitation / Reluctance
definition: Expresses a lack of readiness or a pause before committing to an action.

title: Avoidance
definition: The intent to deliberately stay away from or prevent an action, topic, or outcome.

title: Conditional Intent
definition: Expresses a readiness to act, contingent upon a specific condition being met.
examples: willing to... if|prepared to, provided that|I will, as long as

title: Speculative Intent
definition: Expresses a possible future action that is not yet planned or committed to.

title: Aspiration
definition: Expresses a strong hope or ambition to achieve something, often a long-term goal.

title: Direct Cause ('because')
definition: Indicates the direct reason or cause for an action or state.

title: Purpose ('in order to')
definition: Specifies the intended goal or purpose of an action.
examples: in order to|so that|for the purpose of|with the aim of

title: Consequence ('therefore')
definition: Links a cause to its logical result or consequence.

title: Explanation ('that's why')
definition: Frames a statement as the explanation for a previously mentioned fact or situation.

title: Precondition ('based on')
definition: Indicates that an action or conclusion is founded upon a prior event, reason, or piece of evidence.
examples: based on|on the grounds of|stemming from

title: Enabling Factor ('thanks to')
definition: Attributes an outcome to a positive contributing cause or enabling condition.

title: Motivation ('driven by')
definition: Specifies the internal drive, desire, or motivation behind an action.
examples: motivated by|driven by|out of a desire to

title: Counteracting Cause ('despite')
definition: Indicates a factor that was present but overcome for the result to occur.

title: Hindering Factor ('hindered by')
definition: Specifies a cause that made an action more difficult or prevented a better outcome.
examples: hindered by|hampered by|impeded by|but for the obstacle of

title: Instrumental Cause ('by means of')
definition: Specifies the tool, method, or instrument used to achieve a result.

title: Justification ('as per')
definition: Cites a rule, policy, or principle as the reason for an action.
examples: as per|in accordance with|by definition|as mandated by

title: Attribution ('attributed to')
definition: Assigns the origin or cause of something to a specific source or entity.

title: Origin ('originating from')
definition: Specifies the starting point or source from which something developed.

title: Inferred Cause ('implies')
definition: Suggests a likely cause based on indirect evidence; a weaker form of cau001.
examples: implying that|suggesting|which seems to be because

title: Final Cause ('for the sake of')
definition: Expresses the ultimate end or principle for which an action is done.
examples: for the sake of|in the name of|for the good of

title: Obligation ('must')
definition: Expresses a requirement or necessity for an action to be performed.

title: Permission ('may')
definition: Expresses that an action is allowed or permitted.

title: Prohibition ('must not')
definition: Expresses that an action is forbidden or not allowed.

title: Recommendation ('should')
definition: Expresses that an action is advised or recommended, but not strictly required.

title: Possibility ('can be')
definition: Expresses that a state or event is possible or could occur.

title: Necessity ('is necessary')
definition: Expresses that a state or action is logically necessary or essential.

title: Ability ('is able to')
definition: Expresses the capacity or capability to perform an action.
examples: is able to|capable of|has the ability to

title: Inability ('cannot')
definition: Expresses the lack of capacity or capability to perform an action.

title: Exemption / Non-obligation
definition: Expresses that there is no requirement for an action to be performed; it is optional.
examples: not required to|optional|exempt from|don't have to

title: Advisability ('advisable')
definition: A weaker form of recommendation, suggesting a prudent or wise course of action.
examples: advisable|it would be wise to|prudent to

title: Strong Recommendation ('highly advised')
definition: A forceful recommendation that borders on an obligation due to its benefits or the risks of ignoring it.
examples: highly recommended|strongly advised|it is best to

title: Implicit Permission ('feel free to')
definition: An informal or implicit granting of permission, often used to encourage an action.
examples: feel free to|don't hesitate to|go ahead and

title: Inferential Necessity ('must be')
definition: Expresses a conclusion that is necessarily true based on available evidence.
examples: must be|it has to be|that must mean

title: Speculative Possibility ('could be')
definition: Expresses a possibility based on speculation or a lack of prohibitive evidence.

title: Improbability ('unlikely to')
definition: Expresses that an action or event has a low probability of occurring.
examples: unlikely to|probably not|doubtful that it will

title: Expresses that an ability is contingent on a specific condition being met.
definition: can... if|able to... provided that|can, as long as

title: Expresses a hypothetical or imagined action or outcome, often in a conditional context.
definition: would|would be|in that case... would

title: Expresses a hypothetical outcome in the past that did not happen because its conditions were not met.
definition: would have|could have|should have

title: Initialize / Setup
definition: To prepare a system or process for its first use; to set initial values.

title: Finalize / Commit
definition: To complete the last steps of a process and save the result in a permanent state.

title: Revert / Rollback
definition: To return something to a previous state, undoing changes.

title: Sync / Synchronize
definition: To cause two or more things to exist in the same state or occur at the same time.

title: Iterate / Loop
definition: To perform an action repeatedly, often with incremental changes.

title: Resume / Continue
definition: To begin again after a pause or interruption.

title: Pending / Awaiting
definition: Aspect: in a state of waiting for a trigger, input, or decision before proceeding.

title: Blocked / Obstructed
definition: Aspect: in a state where progress is prevented by an external dependency or obstacle.

title: Queued / Staged
definition: Aspect: formally placed in a sequence or holding area to be processed in order.

title: Conjunction ('and')
definition: Connects two elements, indicating that both are to be considered together or sequentially.

title: Disjunction ('or')
definition: Connects two elements, presenting them as alternatives.

title: Contrast ('but')
definition: Connects two elements, introducing a contrast, exception, or contradiction.

title: Negated Conjunction ('nor')
definition: Used to continue a negative statement, connecting a further negative item.

title: Sequential ('then')
definition: Connects two actions or events, indicating that the second follows the first in time or order.

title: Inference ('so')
definition: Connects a premise to its direct logical conclusion or result.

title: Equivalence ('means')
definition: States that two propositions are logically equivalent or have the same meaning.
examples: means|is equivalent to|if and only if|iff

title: Exclusive Disjunction ('xor')
definition: Connects two alternatives, indicating that one and only one is true.
examples: xor|either/or but not both|one or the other

title: Inclusive Alternative ('and/or')
definition: Connects two elements, explicitly allowing for one, the other, or both to be true.

title: Specification ('namely')
definition: Introduces a more specific or detailed explanation of the preceding statement.

title: Emphasis ('in fact')
definition: Introduces a statement that emphasizes, confirms, or adds force to the previous one.
examples: in fact|indeed|as a matter of fact|actually

title: Similarity ('like')
definition: Asserts that two entities share similar qualities or characteristics.

title: Difference ('unlike')
definition: Asserts that two entities have different qualities or characteristics.

title: Equivalence ('as...as')
definition: Establishes an equivalence of a specific quality between two entities.

title: Superiority ('better than')
definition: Ranks one entity as being of a higher quality or value than another.

title: Inferiority ('worse than')
definition: Ranks one entity as being of a lower quality or value than another.
examples: worse than|inferior to|is not as good as

title: Comparative ('than')
definition: The core relational operator used for direct comparison of adjectives (e.g., faster than, smaller than).

title: Preference ('prefer...over')
definition: Expresses a subjective preference for one entity over another.

title: Superlative (Highest)
definition: Identifies an entity as having the highest degree of a quality among a set.

title: Superlative (Lowest)
definition: Identifies an entity as having the lowest degree of a quality among a set.

title: Exact Match
definition: Asserts that two entities are perfectly identical or equivalent.
examples: exactly the same as|identical to|perfect match

title: Approximation
definition: States that two entities are nearly, but not exactly, the same or equal.

title: Proportionality
definition: Expresses that two quantities or qualities vary in relation to each other.

title: Disproportion
definition: Expresses that two quantities or qualities are out of scale with each other.
examples: disproportionate to|out of proportion with|not to scale

title: Non-comparable
definition: Explicitly states that two entities cannot be meaningfully compared.

title: Speed (Fast)
definition: Indicates an action is performed at a high speed.

title: Speed (Slow)
definition: Indicates an action is performed at a low speed.

title: Care (Careful)
definition: Indicates an action is performed with care, caution, and attention to detail.

title: Care (Careless)
definition: Indicates an action is performed without sufficient attention or care.

title: Intensity (Gentle)
definition: Indicates an action is performed with a soft, mild, or light touch.

title: Intensity (Forceful)
definition: Indicates an action is performed with strength, force, or intensity.

title: Clarity (Clear)
definition: Indicates an action (often communicative) is performed in a clear and understandable way.

title: Stealth (Secretive)
definition: Indicates an action is performed quietly, secretly, or without being noticed.

title: Method (Automatic)
definition: Indicates an action is performed automatically or systematically, without direct manual intervention.

title: Method (Manual)
definition: Indicates an action is performed by a person, directly by hand.

title: Method (Random)
definition: Indicates an action is performed without a clear method or in a random order.

title: Method (Direct)
definition: Indicates an action is performed directly, without intermediaries or indirection.

title: Effort (Easy)
definition: Indicates an action is performed with little to no difficulty.

title: Effort (Difficult)
definition: Indicates an action is performed with great effort or difficulty.

title: Social (Polite)
definition: Indicates an action is performed in a polite, courteous, or respectful manner.

title: Social (Rude)
definition: Indicates an action is performed in a rude, abrupt, or impolite manner.

title: Social (Formal)
definition: Indicates an action is performed in a formal or official capacity.

title: Social (Casual)
definition: Indicates an action is performed in a casual or informal manner.

title: Completeness (Complete)
definition: Indicates an action is performed to its full extent.

title: Completeness (Partial)
definition: Indicates an action is performed in part, but not to its full extent.

title: Volition (Intentional)
definition: Indicates an action is performed deliberately or on purpose.

title: Volition (Accidental)
definition: Indicates an action is performed by chance or by mistake.

title: Vision ('see')
definition: To perceive something with the eyes or through sight.

title: Audition ('hear')
definition: To perceive sound with the ears.

title: Touch ('feel')
definition: To perceive something through physical contact or sensation.

title: Smell ('smell')
definition: To perceive an odor or scent with the nose.

title: Taste ('taste')
definition: To perceive the flavor of something with the tongue.

title: Notice / Become Aware
definition: To become conscious of something through observation or sensory input.

title: Appearance ('seems')
definition: To give the impression of being in a certain state or having a certain quality.
examples: seems|appears to be|looks like|comes across as

title: Imperceptible
definition: Describes something that cannot be sensed or noticed.

title: Glimpse / Fleeting View
definition: To see something briefly or partially.

title: Stare / Gaze
definition: To look at something fixedly and intently, for a prolonged period.

title: Scan / Survey
definition: To look at all parts of something carefully in order to detect a particular feature.

title: Recognize / Identify
definition: To identify someone or something from having encountered them before; to know again.

title: Mishear
definition: To fail to hear a person's words correctly.

title: Internal Sensation (Interoception)
definition: To feel a physical sensation originating from inside the body.

title: Sense / Intuition
definition: To have a feeling or impression about a situation without logical evidence.
examples: sense (a mood, danger)|intuit|get a vibe|have a gut feeling

title: Misperception / Illusion
definition: The act of perceiving something in a way that is not in accordance with reality.

title: High Degree / Intensifier
definition: A general-purpose intensifier for qualities and emotions.

title: Moderate Degree
definition: Indicates a medium or fair level of a quality.

title: Low Degree / Diminisher
definition: A general-purpose diminisher for qualities and emotions.

title: Reliability
definition: The attribute of being consistently good in quality or performance; able to be trusted.

title: Plan / Strategy
definition: An entity representing a detailed proposal or method for doing something.

title: Proposal / Suggestion
definition: An entity representing a plan or action put forward for consideration.

title: Sigh
definition: An audible exhalation expressing sadness, weariness, relief, or frustration.

title: Shrug
definition: A gesture indicating doubt, ignorance, or indifference.

title: Nod
definition: A gesture of the head indicating agreement, affirmation, or acknowledgment.

title: Head Shake
definition: A gesture of the head indicating disagreement, refusal, or disapproval.

title: Eye Roll
definition: A gesture indicating disbelief, annoyance, or contempt.

title: Laughter
definition: A vocal expression of amusement or mirth.

title: Pause / Ellipsis
definition: A pause in speech or writing, often indicating hesitation, thought, or an unfinished idea.

title: Thinking Face
definition: A gesture or emoji indicating contemplation, skepticism, or deep thought.

title: Thumbs Up
definition: A gesture of approval, agreement, or confirmation.

title: Wink
definition: A gesture indicating a joke, secret, or flirtation.

title: Facepalm
definition: A gesture of frustration, disbelief, or embarrassment.

title: Clapping / Applause
definition: A gesture of approval, praise, or celebration.

title: Heart / Affection
definition: An expression of love, affection, or strong approval.

title: Celebration
definition: An expression of joy or celebration for an event or achievement.

title: Gasp
definition: A sharp intake of breath indicating surprise, shock, or alarm.

title: Groan / Grumble
definition: A low sound of pain, displeasure, or disapproval.

title: Tsk / Disapproval
definition: A clicking sound with the tongue to express disapproval or sympathy.

title: Ahem / Clearing Throat
definition: The act of clearing one's throat to get attention, express awkwardness, or signal a correction.

title: Salute
definition: A gesture of respect, acknowledgment, or farewell, often formal or military-style.

title: Wave
definition: A gesture of greeting or farewell.

title: Awkward Silence
definition: A noticeable and uncomfortable pause in a conversation.

title: Mumbling / Inaudible
definition: Speech that is low, indistinct, and difficult to understand.
